(40, 11, 8, 40, 3, 4, 4, 'a man clothed in soft raiment', 'Contrast of Clothing and Lifestyle', 'This connection highlights the contrast between John the Baptist''s austere lifestyle and the expectation of a prophet. Both passages emphasize the nature of true prophetic identity, with Matthew 11:8 questioning the allure of soft clothing found in kings'' houses, while Matthew 3:4 describes John''s rough attire.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
