(40, 11, 10, 42, 7, 26, 27, 'Behold, I send my messenger before thy face, which shall prepare thy way before thee.', 'Connection of Messenger Prophecy', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the messenger who prepares the way. They quote the same prophecy about sending a messenger before one''s face.', 'quotation', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 10, 43, 1, 23, 23, 'prepare thy way before thee', 'Connection of Messengers', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a messenger preparing the way for the Lord. Matthew refers to a messenger sent before, while John identifies himself as the voice crying in the wilderness, echoing this preparatory theme.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
